		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Root vs. Snare<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 7:10 AM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=11&mid=9666834216185&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=11&mid=9666834216185&num=7&post=1&replyto=9666834216185"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>  | <a class=sm href="mailto:Daeanor@allakhazam.com">Email User</a> <a name=9666834216185></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=483"><span id=Scholar>Daeanor</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>46 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I hear from everyone how bad they think root is, and how they would rather use onds of Force to snare a critter, then kite it. That works well enough if you are killing multiples with AE spells, but for a single mob, I still prefer root.<br><br>For one thing, if you don't have SoW, or yours gives out, it is far too easy to catch yourself with Bonds when refreshing it. It has a fairly short range compared to your DD's. For another, if you are kiting, you may not see somthing else may have gotten near your mob that you don't want Bonds to catch (like drixies or pilgrims in FV).<br><br>I start out a single battle with root (Immobilize, now that I have it). If it sicks, I nuke away until it break or the mob is dead - nothing special there. If not, or if it breaks beofre he critter drops, I just stand my ground and keep trying. If it is a mob that stunns reliably, stun, and back off while spells are cycling, then root again. Once the mob is rooted, back off to maximum distance to nuke away. Roots seem to stick easier on stunned mobs. Repeat all as necessary. Keep your best skin spell up, while it is in effect, it is much less likely you will be interupted (to say nothing of not getting hurt). If the skin gets beat off you, next root, refresh it.<br><br>Yes, sometimes your luck is just awful, but when things get nasty, whatever your best version of Shadow-Step is, cast that and either run or gate. It has saved me many times. </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Daeanor Endarion<br>Arcanist of the Rathe</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >7 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
