		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=355514"><span id=>Shazwauza</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hehe...ohhh boy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Why does it always have to be one or the other?  If you are anything like me and can't decide which you rather use, try both!  Why root vs snare? They do stack... oh.. yeah they dooo.<br><br>Comprise your spell list of 1 high damage spell (the best nuke you have for your level) 1 med damage spell, 1 low level damage spell (why? to get rid of that annoying last 1-8% the mob has and to conserve mana. don't wanna use you 400 mana spell that drops the mobs % by 25% when you can use a 150 mana spell to finish it off.  why med if you don't have too *wink*), Your best stunning spell, Root spell, BoF snaring spell, Harvest (if you have it) and Gate.<br><br>What I like to do is start off using BoF(snare) immediately slow the mobs movement speed.  Quickly after hit it with your best root spell (Currently for me it is Paralyzing Earth: a 3min root).  Both spells are cost little mana and help a Wizzy immensely.  After this I cast my stunning spell (either Clash spell will work)...this is cause from my experience the mob about 90% of the time will always break root on first spell no matter what.  So if your root breaks after this spell, good, root him again while he is stunned. The second root's break % seems to be a little more in your favor (not always though hehe).  After this get some distance and start nuking away...if root breaks again the BoF spell should keep his speed low enought that he won't be able to close the gap between you and him before you can root again. And resume nuking.<br><br>This is a strategy that has worked for me soloing in open and tight places.  Oh and single only too.  Another good thing about this combo if you run low on mana your root should allow you to sit and med up enough for a nuke or two while you tease your mob.  Once the mob is dead kick him once while its down, take his personal property and pick your next victim. =D<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Accepting a challenge is the first step.<br>Achieving that challenge and seeing it through is a step in the right direction. ;)<br><br>Shazwauza<br>51 Channeler (Froglok)<br>Cazic-Thule Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8>Posting from Saint George UT, USA</td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
